-- Scotiabank Has ‘Appetite’ for Selective Takeovers, Porter Says
-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 2013-09-25T12:49:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-25/scotiabank-has-appetite-for-selective-takeovers-porter-says.html
Bank of Nova Scotia  President  Brian Porter  says he has an “appetite” for selective acquisitions.  Porter, who becomes chief executive officer of Canada’s
third-biggest bank on Nov. 1, made the comment today during the
lender’s wealth management and insurance investor day
presentation in Toronto.  To contact the reporter on this story:
